A '''borganism''' is an organization of autonomous organisms, usually called ''units'', who have merged their individual wills to create one, collectively conscious being. The word derives from [[borg|The Borg]], a borganism in the fictional [[Star Trek]] universe.

In [[biology]], such an organization, for example a bee hive, is usually called a [[superorganism]].

In the fictional [[Star Trek]] universe [[borg|The Borg]] is a collective group of organisms which have been technologically augmented, producing a collective consciousness as an emergent phenomenon of the networking.

Among [[anarchocapitalism|anarchocapitalist]] and [[transhumanism|transhuman]] [[libertarianism|libertarians]], the government is often seen as a proto-borganism, especially governments like that of the [[Soviet Union]].

